29static const int FORMAT_INFO_MASK_QR = 0x5412;
30
31/**
32* See ISO 18004:2006, Annex C, Table C.1
33*/
34static const std::array<int, 2> FORMAT_INFO_DECODE_LOOKUP[] = {
35 0x5412, 0x00,
36 0x5125, 0x01,
37 0x5E7C, 0x02,
38 0x5B4B, 0x03,
39 0x45F9, 0x04,
40 0x40CE, 0x05,
41 0x4F97, 0x06,
42 0x4AA0, 0x07,
43 0x77C4, 0x08,
44 0x72F3, 0x09,
45 0x7DAA, 0x0A,
46 0x789D, 0x0B,
47 0x662F, 0x0C,
48 0x6318, 0x0D,
49 0x6C41, 0x0E,
50 0x6976, 0x0F,
51 0x1689, 0x10,
52 0x13BE, 0x11,
53 0x1CE7, 0x12,
54 0x19D0, 0x13,
55 0x0762, 0x14,
56 0x0255, 0x15,
57 0x0D0C, 0x16,
58 0x083B, 0x17,
59 0x355F, 0x18,
60 0x3068, 0x19,
61 0x3F31, 0x1A,
62 0x3A06, 0x1B,
63 0x24B4, 0x1C,
64 0x2183, 0x1D,
65 0x2EDA, 0x1E,
66 0x2BED, 0x1F,
67};

71FormatInformation::FormatInformation(int formatInfo)
72{
73 // Bits 3,4
74 _errorCorrectionLevel = ECLevelFromBits((formatInfo >> 3) & 0x03);
75 // Bottom 3 bits
76 _dataMask = static_cast<uint8_t>(formatInfo & 0x07);
77}
78
79/**
80* @param maskedFormatInfo1 format info indicator, with mask still applied
81* @param maskedFormatInfo2 second copy of same info; both are checked at the same time
82* to establish best match
83* @return information about the format it specifies, or {@code null}
84* if doesn't seem to match any known pattern
85*/
86FormatInformation
87FormatInformation::DecodeFormatInformation(int maskedFormatInfo1, int maskedFormatInfo2)
88{
89 auto result = DoDecodeFormatInformation(maskedFormatInfo1, maskedFormatInfo2);
90
91 if (!result.isValid())
92 // Should return null, but, some QR codes apparently
93 // do not mask this info. Try again by actually masking the pattern
94 // first
95 result = DoDecodeFormatInformation(maskedFormatInfo1 ^ FORMAT_INFO_MASK_QR, maskedFormatInfo2 ^ FORMAT_INFO_MASK_QR);
96
97 return result;
98}
99
100FormatInformation
101FormatInformation::DoDecodeFormatInformation(int maskedFormatInfo1, int maskedFormatInfo2)
102{
103 // Find the int in FORMAT_INFO_DECODE_LOOKUP with fewest bits differing
104 int bestDifference = std::numeric_limits<int>::max();
105 int bestFormatInfo = 0;
106 for (auto& decodeInfo : FORMAT_INFO_DECODE_LOOKUP) {
107 int targetInfo = decodeInfo[0];
108 if (targetInfo == maskedFormatInfo1 || targetInfo == maskedFormatInfo2) {
109 // Found an exact match
110 return {decodeInfo[1]};
111 }
112 int bitsDifference = BitHacks::CountBitsSet(maskedFormatInfo1 ^ targetInfo);
113 if (bitsDifference < bestDifference) {
114 bestFormatInfo = decodeInfo[1];
115 bestDifference = bitsDifference;
116 }
117 if (maskedFormatInfo1 != maskedFormatInfo2) {
118 // also try the other option
119 bitsDifference = BitHacks::CountBitsSet(maskedFormatInfo2 ^ targetInfo);
120 if (bitsDifference < bestDifference) {
121 bestFormatInfo = decodeInfo[1];
122 bestDifference = bitsDifference;
123 }
124 }
125 }
126 // Hamming distance of the 32 masked codes is 7, by construction, so <= 3 bits
127 // differing means we found a match
128 if (bestDifference <= 3) {
129 return {bestFormatInfo};
130 }
131 return {};
132}
